dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Marsh c Morkel b Steyn 67 (88b 3x4 2x6 121m) SR: 76.13

dismissalComment.html: it is hard to clear Morne Morkel wherever he is, he is at short fine leg, this is a slower one into the pad, and Marsh has flicked it for Morkel to take it over his head

dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey c du Plessis b Philander 25 (45b 2x4 0x6 57m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: Philander strikes immediately on comeback, and that is a fine catch by Faf, another one falls to the pull, Bailey wasn't on top of the stroke as he hit it off the front foot low to Faf at mid on, and he went down to pouch it

that is a very sharp take from the keeper down the leg side, given not out, and South Africa review, no problems with Morkel's front foot, this is a proper lifter, has bounced sharply and thudded into Warner's glove, the umpires are pretty sure as they check HotSpot, and Warner is almost past the boundary by the time the umpire raises his finger

that is probably not the best stroke to play at this stage, Morkel bangs it in short of a length, Smith tries to force a pull, and Tahir takes the steepling top edge after moving to his left from mid on, mid off was around too, but Tahir hung on in the end, wasn't really the length for the pull

Keeper and bowler are convinced about the caught behind, umpire isnt, de Kock is pushing for the review immediately, and South Africa are doing that, Wade on the hop to a short of a length ball into the ribcage, it has brushed his shirt, third umpire says that is close to the glove, and wants to look at HotSpot, there is a faint remark on the bottom of the glove, they move on to Snicko, umpire wants to look at front angle again now, says he is happy with that shot, wants to go back to HotSpot now, says there is a mark, and goes back to the onfield umpire to tell him about the HotSpot mark, and asks him to change the decision to out

it is coming apart for Australia, as Morkel removes Maxwell for a duck, he was on his toes trying to run this short of a length ball towards third man, ends up playing on, again, you have to say that is not a good choice of stroke off your second ball
five for Morkel, and he jumps in celebration, Johnson stuck on the crease to one that leaves him with the angle close to off, and nicks it through to the keeper

he's gone this time, and the bowling change working, it is the taller Morkel who is positioned at mid on, Finch drives this angled length delivery on the up, and Morkel stretches his hands over his head to take it, Steyn pumps his fist and lets out a roar

nine down, Faf in business at mid on again, a length ball around middle and off, Coulter-Nile whips it for a tumbling Faf to take his second catch, not easy to pull off these shots with the pace and bounce in the pitch

first one down, Watson the man at first slip who jumps high to catch this thick edge of a cut, was short and wide from Hazlewood, replays show a fly was bothering de Kock, and had settled close to his left eye as he lined up to play that cut
Hazlewood has struck, this is a steep bouncer, Faf wants to hook, but he has only managed a thin edge through to Wade
he's lasted one ball, Hazlewood has two in two, not as short as the one that got Faf, but a lifter outside off nevertheless, Behardien hops and awkwardly fends it, straight to gully

commentTextItems.html: Steyn does it by clearing front leg and whacking this length delivery over the bowler

commentPostTextItems.html: That is all from this game. Good bye

AB de Villiers: "Little angry with myself for getting out. Those totals are always tricky to chase. I like to be positive when I come into situations. I was confident in the boys. I was not happy that I let them down. I love to finish games. Felt the guys were calm to start with and recognised the key moments. Very happy for Morne Morkel. Behardien really played his role today."

Bailey: "Just not enough runs. I can't remember getting too many drives and cuts, it was the pressure that built up. Large gap between our best and worst at the moment." Bailey says it was a combination of good bowling from South Africa and poor batting from Australia, adding that many of his batsmen could not say they had got out to great deliveries.

Morne Morkel is the Man of the Match. Morkel: "To start well was important, in that first over. Always love to bowl at the WACA with the bounce. To take a five-for against this quality line-up is going into the memory bank for me."

Australia fighting till the end but they just didn't have the runs. Rossouw calmed the early nerves with a polished 30, AB took over and twinkled his way to 48 off 41, and Miller kept his nerve in the end with an unbeaten 22. The series is tied 1-1 going into the third game in Canberra
Selwood: "In the end it was all about the C-word again for South Africa. But today that C-word was Coulter-Nile, and it won them the game"

commentTextItems.html: backs away, swishes and misses, Wade goes up for caught behind in hope
angled in good length to Steyn, who pushes it away safely

pings short extra cover as he middles another full delivery
four more for Miller, Coulter-Nile overpitches, and Miller eases it between extra cover and mid off
swivels and pulls hard, but he's not middled it, and it has not gone far from midwicket
rides the bounc on this back of a length ball to drop it into the pitch
turned off the pad behind square for two more
Miller almost settles the issue as he leans into another drive, closing the face to a pitched up delivery around off to drive it past the non-striker

shortish and down the pads, AB swings it down to fine leg

he pitches it up last ball of the over, but Miller is up to it, he leans forward and dispatches it through vacant mid off
another bouncer, Miller sways inside the line, it is called a no-ball as Johnson has bowled one too many for the over

dismissalComment.html: first one down, Watson the man at first slip who jumps high to catch this thick edge of a cut, was short and wide from Hazlewood, replays show a fly was bothering de Kock, and had settled close to his left eye as he lined up to play that cut

dismissalText.commentary: Hashim Amla c Wade b Johnson 10 (22b 1x4 0x6 30m) SR: 45.45

dismissalComment.html: they have the big one, Amla arched back and tried to upper cut this bouncer over the cordon, only managed an edge through to the keeper

dismissalText.commentary: Rilee Rossouw c Smith b Maxwell 30 (25b 6x4 0x6 31m) SR: 120

dismissalComment.html: Maxwell has taken a wicket in his first over, Rossouw has gone hard at a tossed up, full and wide ball, and the thick edge has flown to Smith at slip

dismissalText.commentary: Faf du Plessis c Wade b Hazlewood 19 (39b 2x4 0x6 81m) SR: 48.71

dismissalComment.html: Hazlewood has struck, this is a steep bouncer, Faf wants to hook, but he has only managed a thin edge through to Wade

dismissalText.commentary: Farhaan Behardien c Warner b Hazlewood 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: he's lasted one ball, Hazlewood has two in two, not as short as the one that got Faf, but a lifter outside off nevertheless, Behardien hops and awkwardly fends it, straight to gully

dismissalText.commentary: AB de Villiers c Wade b Hazlewood 48 (41b 8x4 0x6 61m) SR: 117.07

dismissalComment.html: this game is not done yet, AB is gone now, AB chipped out and tried to drive, only to thick edge it through to the keeper, Hazlewood has his fourth

dismissalText.commentary: Vernon Philander c Johnson b Hazlewood 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: five for Hazlewood as he makes Philander jump with a steep bouncer, it pops up towards gully, who takes it safely despite Warner running almost in his way from the slips
